Procedure (Fisrt Install Eclipse JEE and Tomcat ) :-

1. Install Eclispe JEE( http://www.eclipse.org/downloads/packages/release/indigo/sr2/eclipse-ide-java-ee-developers )
2. Install Tomcat apache version 7 ( https://tomcat.apache.org/download-70.cgi ) 
3. Open Eclipse on JEE Perpective mode 
4. Click Servers in console 
5. Expand Apache
6. Select tomcat version 7 
7. Click Next (here we need to add the Tomcat path)
8. After downloading Tomcat server, go and copy the tomcat path ( Should copy the path before bin ) 
9. Paste this path in tomcat installation
10. Click Next 
11. Click Finish 
12. Check console (tomcat v 7 and start ) 
13. Double click for changing the port 8080

Procedure to create web applications:-

1. Select file in menu (Eclipse) 
2. Visit New 
3. Select Dynamic web project
4. Assign the your Project Name Ex:( web1)
5. Click Finish 
6. Open the project 
7. right click and create new html file(index.html) 
8. Go to console (servers) 
9. right click tomcat v7 
10. go to add and remove 
11. select web1 (project) 
12. Add the project 
13. click finish 
14. Go to console tomcat v7 
15. right click and restart the server 
16. Open your browser 
17. Types ( localhost:8080/web1) to view you web applications

Procedure to create servlet:-

1.Right click your project 
2. visit new 
3. visit servlet 
4. Type class name Ex( MyServlet) 
5. click finish
6. you can test your servlet code here (MyServlet.java)

Thank you




